label: Lower frequency bound
rdfs_comment: The lowest frequency of the phenomena reflected in the multimedia item or Region of Interest.
dcterms_description: This term refers to the sound events depicted and not to the constraints of the recording medium, so are in principle independent from sampleRate. If dwc:scientificName is specified and if applied to the entire multimedia item, these frequency bounds refer to the sounds of the species given in the dwc:scientificName throughout the whole recording. Although many users will specify both freqLow and freqHigh, it is permitted to specify just one or the other, for example if only one of the bounds is discernible.

label: Upper frequency bound
rdfs_comment: The highest frequency of the phenomena reflected in the multimedia item or Region of Interest.
dcterms_description: This term refers to the sound events depicted and not to the constraints of the recording medium, so are in principle independent from sampleRate. If dwc:scientificName is specified and if applied to the entire multimedia item, these frequency bounds refer to the sounds of the species given in the dwc:scientificName throughout the whole recording. Although many users will specify both freqLow and freqHigh, it is permitted to specify just one or the other, for example if only one of the bounds is discernible.

label: Region of Interest Class
rdfs_comment: A designated region of a media item bounded in dimensions appropriate for the media type.
dcterms_description: Dimensions may include spatial, temporal, or frequency bounds.

label: Has Region of Interest
rdfs_comment: A region of interest located within the subject media item.
skos_scopeNote: ac:hasROI is the inverse property of ac:isROIOf.
dcterms_description: Used to link a subject media item to an object region of interest.

label: Is Region of Interest of
rdfs_comment: The media item within which a region of interest is located.
skos_scopeNote: ac:isROIOf is the inverse property of ac:hasROI.
dcterms_description: Used to link a subject region of interest to an object media item.

label: Fractional X
rdfs_comment: The horizontal position of a reference point, measured from the left side of the media item and expressed as a decimal fraction of the width of the media item.
skos_scopeNote: A valid value MUST be greater than or equal to zero and less than or equal to one. The precision of this value SHOULD be great enough that when the ac:xFrac value is multiplied by the exif:PixelXDimension of the Best Quality variant of the Service Access point, rounding to the nearest integer results in the same horizontal pixel location originally used to define the point.
dcterms_description: This point can serve as the horizontal position of the upper left corner of a bounding rectangle, or as the center of a circle.

label: Fractional Y
rdfs_comment: The vertical position of a reference point, measured from the top of the media item and expressed as a decimal fraction of the height of the media item.
skos_scopeNote: A valid value MUST be greater than or equal to zero and less than or equal to one. The precision of this value SHOULD be great enough that when the ac:yFrac value is multiplied by the exif:PixelYDimension of the Best Quality variant of the Service Access point, rounding to the nearest integer results in the same vertical pixel originally used to define the point.
dcterms_description: This point can serve as the vertical position of the upper left corner of a bounding rectangle, or as the center of a circle.

label: Fractional Width
rdfs_comment: The width of the bounding rectangle, expressed as a decimal fraction of the width of the media item.
skos_scopeNote: The sum of a valid value plus ac:xFrac MUST be greater than zero and less than or equal to one. The precision of this value SHOULD be great enough that when ac:widthFrac and ac:xFrac are used with the exif:PixelXDimension of the Best Quality variant of the Service Access point to calculate the lower right corner of the rectangle, rounding to the nearest integer results in the same horizontal pixel originally used to define the point. This term MUST NOT be used with ac:radius to define a region of interest.
dcterms_description: Zero-sized bounding rectangles are not allowed. To designate a point, use the radius option with a zero value.

label: Fractional Height
rdfs_comment: The height of the bounding rectangle, expressed as a decimal fraction of the height of the media item.
skos_scopeNote: The sum of a valid value plus ac:yFrac MUST be greater than zero and less than or equal to one. The precision of this value SHOULD be great enough that when ac:heightFrac and ac:yFrac are used with the exif:PixelYDimension of the Best Quality variant of the Service Access point to calculate the lower right corner of the rectangle, rounding to the nearest integer results in the same vertical pixel originally used to define the point. This term MUST NOT be used with ac:radius to define a region of interest.
dcterms_description: Zero-sized bounding rectangles are not allowed. To designate a point, use the radius option with a zero value.

label: Radius
rdfs_comment: The radius of a bounding circle or arc, expressed as a fraction of the width of the media item.
skos_scopeNote: A valid value MUST be greater than or equal to zero. A valid value MAY cause the designated circle to extend beyond the bounds of the media item. In that case, the arc within the media item plus the bounds of the media item specify the region of interest. This term MUST NOT be used with ac:widthFrac or ac:heightFrac to define a region of interest.
dcterms_description: This term may be used with ac:xFrac and ac:yFrac to define a point. In that case, the implication is that the point falls on some object of interest within the media item, but nothing more can be assumed about the bounds of that object.

label: Start Timestamp
rdfs_comment: The beginning of a temporal region, specified as real-world clock time ISO 8601 timestamps, using UTC timezone, with an optional fractional part to indicate milliseconds or finer. There is no limit on the number of decimal places for the decimal fraction.
skos_scopeNote: This term MAY be applied to a region of interest or an entire media item.

label: End Timestamp
rdfs_comment: The end of a temporal region, specified as real-world clock time ISO 8601 timestamps, using UTC timezone, with an optional fractional part to indicate milliseconds or finer. There is no limit on the number of decimal places for the decimal fraction.
skos_scopeNote: This term MAY be applied to a region of interest or an entire media item.

label: Media Duration
rdfs_comment: The playback duration of an audio or video file in seconds.
dcterms_description: This might be different from the time in seconds calculated as the difference of ac:endTimestamp and ac:startTimestamp if ac:mediaSpeed is not equal to 1.

label: Media Speed
rdfs_comment: The decimal fraction representing the natural speed over the encoded speed.
skos_scopeNote: If a value for ac:mediaSpeed is not provided, applications SHOULD assume that 1.0 is the value.
dcterms_description: For example, in a time-lapse recording where 60 seconds of natural time is represented in 1 second of media this would be 60. In a time-expanded recording where 1 second of recording is represented in 5 seconds of media, this would be 0.2.

label: Frame Rate
rdfs_comment: The decimal fraction representing the frequency (rate) at which consecutive images (frames) were captured in real time for a moving image, expressed as the number of frames per second.
skos_scopeNote: This term represents the rate at which consecutive images were captured in real time, not the rate at which the media is encoded to play back the recording.
dcterms_description: For example, in a recording where 60 consecutive images (frames) are captured for each second of the real-time recording, this would be 60. In a time-lapse recording where one image (frame) is recorded every 5 seconds of recording, this would be 0.2.

label: Start Time in Seconds
rdfs_comment: The beginning of a temporal region, specified as an absolute offset relative to the beginning of the media item (this corresponds to Normal Play Time RFC 2326), specified as seconds, with an optional fractional part to indicate milliseconds or finer.
skos_scopeNote: This term MUST only be applied to a region of interest.

label: End Time in Seconds
rdfs_comment: The end of a temporal region, specified as an absolute offset relative to the beginning of the media item (this corresponds to Normal Play Time RFC 2326), specified as seconds, with an optional fractional part to indicate milliseconds or finer.
skos_scopeNote: This term MUST only be applied to a region of interest.

label: Caption
rdfs_comment: As alternative or in addition to description, a caption is free-form text to be displayed together with (rather than instead of) a resource that is suitable for captions (especially images).
dcterms_description: If both description and caption are present in the metadata, a description is typically displayed instead of the resource, a caption together with the resource. Thus, in HTML it would be appropriate to use ac:caption values in figcaption elements. Often only one of description or caption is present; choose the term most appropriate for your metadata.
